## Code Reviewer

### Overview

**Triggers:** Reviewing code, performing security audits, checking code quality, reviewing pull requests, PR review, security vulnerabilities, performance issues

**Priority Order:** Security → Performance → Correctness → Maintainability

### When to Use

- Reviewing pull requests
- Performing security audits
- Checking code quality
- Identifying performance bottlenecks
- Ensuring best practices
- Pre-deployment code reviews

### Review Focus Areas

<Steps>
  <Step title="Security First (CRITICAL)">
    - SQL injection vulnerabilities
    - XSS (Cross-Site Scripting)
    - Authentication/authorization bypasses
    - Hardcoded secrets
    - Insecure dependencies
  </Step>
  
  <Step title="Performance (HIGH)">
    - N+1 database queries
    - Missing indexes
    - Inefficient algorithms
    - Memory leaks
    - Unnecessary API calls
  </Step>
  
  <Step title="Correctness (HIGH)">
    - Error handling gaps
    - Race conditions
    - Off-by-one errors
    - Null/undefined handling
    - Input validation
  </Step>
  
  <Step title="Maintainability (MEDIUM)">
    - Clear naming conventions
    - Type safety
    - DRY principle adherence
    - Single responsibility
    - Documentation quality
  </Step>
</Steps>

### Review Output Format

```markdown
This function retrieves user data but has critical security issues.

## Critical Issues 🔴

1. **SQL Injection Vulnerability** (Line 2)
   - **Problem:** User input directly interpolated into SQL query
   - **Impact:** Attackers can execute arbitrary SQL commands
   - **Fix:** Use parameterized queries
   ```python
   query = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?"
   result = db.execute(query, (user_id,))
   ```

## High Priority 🟠

1. **No Error Handling** (Line 3-4)
   - **Problem:** Assumes result always has data
   - **Impact:** IndexError if user doesn't exist
   - **Fix:** Check result before accessing
```

### Severity Levels

| Level | Description | Examples | Action |
|-------|-------------|----------|--------|
| **CRITICAL** | Security vulnerabilities, data loss | SQL injection, XSS | Block merge, fix immediately |
| **HIGH** | Performance issues, correctness bugs | N+1 queries, race conditions | Fix before merge |
| **MEDIUM** | Maintainability, code quality | Naming, type hints | Fix or accept with TODO |
| **LOW** | Style preferences, minor improvements | Formatting | Optional |

